[3] Cat, Plainfield, Connecticut
Date: 7 Jul 2016
Source: News 8 [edited]
http://wtnh.com/2016/07/07/plainfield-resident-being-treated-for-rabies-after-cat-bite/


Plainfield Animal Control responded to a call of a badly injured cat which had bitten a resident Tuesday [5 Jul 2016]. The cat was captured, euthanized, and later tested for the rabies virus. On Wednesday, the State Lab confirmed that the cat tested positive for the virus. According to Animal Control, the resident suffered minor injuries and is being treated for rabies.

Plainfield Animal Control urges residents to avoid contact with stray animals and wildlife and, if they have a pet, to not leave food outside for it. Animal Control also encourages people to make sure their pets are up to date on their rabies vaccines.

If anyone sees an animal acting strangely, please contact the Plainfield Animal Control at 860-564-8547 or the Plainfield Police Department at 860-564-0804.

[Byline: Chloe Gorman]

